1
00:00:02,467 --> 00:00:05,433
I'm going to study hard

2
00:00:05,533 --> 00:00:08,833
and when I graduate,
I want to be a nurse.

3
00:00:09,500 --> 00:00:14,200
I know you'll say it's a job
that involves life and death.

4
00:00:14,600 --> 00:00:17,233
But I really believe in this.

5
00:00:18,867 --> 00:00:19,767
So...

6
00:00:21,167 --> 00:00:22,633
I want to be a nurse.

7
00:00:26,633 --> 00:00:29,700
What do you think?

8
00:00:30,600 --> 00:00:33,667
If I tried to stop you,
you wouldn't listen.

9
00:00:36,900 --> 00:00:37,800
So...

10
00:00:39,100 --> 00:00:40,467
give it a try.

11
00:00:59,900 --> 00:01:01,600
Kinnosuke...

12
00:01:04,400 --> 00:01:06,533
I'm running out of time.

13
00:02:52,567 --> 00:02:58,000
{\an8}MISCHIEVOUS KISS 2

14
00:02:58,100 --> 00:03:03,167
{\an8}EXCITING! MY FIRST DATE

15
00:03:14,767 --> 00:03:16,933
You came.

16
00:03:17,500 --> 00:03:19,500
Congratulations, Matsumoto.

17
00:03:19,567 --> 00:03:20,567
Congratulations!

18
00:03:21,600 --> 00:03:25,433
I heard you're transferring
to the nursing school.

19
00:03:25,500 --> 00:03:26,867
How did you know?

20
00:03:27,300 --> 00:03:28,867
It's a well-known fact.

21
00:03:28,967 --> 00:03:31,967
You're still pursuing Naoki,
even in the medical field.

22
00:03:32,533 --> 00:03:37,433
That makes it sound like
Naoki is my only motivation!

23
00:03:37,767 --> 00:03:38,800
Isn't it?

24
00:03:39,467 --> 00:03:40,867
You, too?

25
00:03:41,733 --> 00:03:44,333
Well, I guess...

26
00:03:44,400 --> 00:03:46,933
So, how did you do on the exam?

27
00:03:53,133 --> 00:03:54,333
Ta-da!

28
00:03:54,867 --> 00:03:57,100
"Congratulations." You passed?

29
00:03:57,167 --> 00:04:02,767
I passed the highly competitive
nursing school examination!

30
00:04:03,500 --> 00:04:06,400
<i>That's right! I did it.</i>

31
00:04:06,500 --> 00:04:09,933
<i>I passed the nursing school</i>
<i>entrance exam!</i>

32
00:04:10,833 --> 00:04:15,000
I don't think it's the best thing
for people but...

33
00:04:15,100 --> 00:04:17,033
I guess congratulations
are in order.

34
00:04:18,233 --> 00:04:21,033
I share your concerns, but...

35
00:04:21,400 --> 00:04:22,667
Naoki!

36
00:04:24,633 --> 00:04:27,967
Oh, well. Good luck, nurse.

37
00:04:32,067 --> 00:04:34,500
You're graduating!

38
00:04:35,400 --> 00:04:36,767
Take care!

39
00:04:36,833 --> 00:04:40,200
Thank you! You too.

40
00:04:45,133 --> 00:04:46,367
You're leaving us.

41
00:04:46,433 --> 00:04:47,700
Bye-bye!

42
00:04:50,167 --> 00:04:51,167
Satomi!

43
00:04:51,233 --> 00:04:52,300
Jinko!

44
00:04:55,967 --> 00:04:59,200
Are those your friends
bawling their eyes out?

45
00:05:00,833 --> 00:05:05,167
Actually... neither of them
are graduating.

46
00:05:05,233 --> 00:05:06,233
They flunked?

47
00:05:07,167 --> 00:05:12,500
Satomi hardly attended an elective
class which turned out to have

48
00:05:12,567 --> 00:05:15,233
strict attendance requirements.

49
00:05:15,300 --> 00:05:21,367
Jinko turned in her brother's homework
instead of her dissertation by mistake.

50
00:05:23,500 --> 00:05:26,133
It sounds unreal, but it's true.

51
00:05:26,900 --> 00:05:28,567
So, they flunked together?

52
00:05:28,633 --> 00:05:29,533
Yeah.

53
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:34,900
They both had job offers and
their boyfriends had graduated.

54
00:05:36,333 --> 00:05:39,467
Your friends are incredible.

55
00:05:40,067 --> 00:05:42,000
I can't bear to watch.

56
00:05:43,367 --> 00:05:45,733
Don't act as if you're above it all.

57
00:05:46,500 --> 00:05:49,000
You would have flunked, too.

58
00:05:49,067 --> 00:05:50,267
Naoki!

59
00:05:51,667 --> 00:05:54,500
Good thing she got into
the nursing school...

60
00:05:55,433 --> 00:06:00,867
I thought I had just enough
credits to graduate

61
00:06:00,933 --> 00:06:04,033
but I made a slight miscalculation.

62
00:06:04,100 --> 00:06:05,833
You shouldn't be laughing.

63
00:06:07,867 --> 00:06:10,133
I can't believe you passed the test.

64
00:06:10,200 --> 00:06:13,500
You can't even count
your credits accurately.

65
00:06:13,567 --> 00:06:15,067
Are you cut out to be a nurse?

66
00:06:15,500 --> 00:06:16,967
I'll be more careful!

67
00:06:17,767 --> 00:06:19,200
God...

68
00:06:19,267 --> 00:06:22,700
All three of you
are unable to graduate.

69
00:06:22,767 --> 00:06:25,067
It's not an easy task.

70
00:06:25,133 --> 00:06:26,933
I'm actually impressed.

71
00:06:27,333 --> 00:06:28,267
How rude.

72
00:06:28,333 --> 00:06:31,500
At least you can all
stay in school together.

73
00:06:32,367 --> 00:06:34,367
You got your dream job.

74
00:06:34,733 --> 00:06:37,567
Yes. I'll be working in the IT industry.

75
00:06:38,367 --> 00:06:42,167
My intention is to work hard
and find the best man out there.

76
00:06:42,500 --> 00:06:44,267
I want to avenge myself.

77
00:06:50,333 --> 00:06:54,700
Here comes your best man
carrying a bouquet of roses.

78
00:07:01,800 --> 00:07:02,867
Out of the question!

79
00:07:06,167 --> 00:07:07,067
Naoki.

80
00:07:08,800 --> 00:07:12,133
Thanks to you, I enjoyed college life.

81
00:07:13,533 --> 00:07:15,133
Become a good doctor, okay?

82
00:07:17,333 --> 00:07:18,367
Thanks.

83
00:07:22,933 --> 00:07:24,067
Miss Aihara.

84
00:07:32,100 --> 00:07:36,633
I had fun with you, too.
Don't hold Naoki back, okay?

85
00:07:38,733 --> 00:07:40,100
I hope you make a good wife.

86
00:07:42,633 --> 00:07:47,233
Thank you! And good luck in IT!

87
00:07:48,700 --> 00:07:49,533
See you.

88
00:07:56,100 --> 00:07:58,000
Hey, Matsumoto!

89
00:08:00,733 --> 00:08:05,033
Congratulations on
joining the ranks of society!

90
00:08:05,967 --> 00:08:07,667
There's nothing between us now.

91
00:08:08,233 --> 00:08:11,267
This is for you.

92
00:08:13,533 --> 00:08:18,500
That's very nice of you,
but I have a party to attend.

93
00:08:23,467 --> 00:08:26,933
Matsumoto! I'm going with you!

94
00:08:28,000 --> 00:08:29,967
Matsumoto! Wait for me!

95
00:08:36,667 --> 00:08:41,133
Kinnosuke will never
have feelings for me.

96
00:08:41,867 --> 00:08:45,933
Kotoko... you're still his only love.

97
00:08:46,000 --> 00:08:49,433
That's not true.
He's just embarrassed.

98
00:08:49,500 --> 00:08:52,067
I'm sure he thinks about you.

99
00:08:53,133 --> 00:08:54,967
Oh, Kotoko.

100
00:08:55,800 --> 00:08:57,000
I...

101
00:08:58,200 --> 00:09:01,500
have to return to England.

102
00:09:02,000 --> 00:09:02,900
What?

103
00:09:03,367 --> 00:09:04,833
But...

104
00:09:04,933 --> 00:09:10,300
if Kinnosuke asked me to stay...

105
00:09:12,200 --> 00:09:13,600
I...

106
00:09:16,933 --> 00:09:17,967
I...

107
00:09:20,133 --> 00:09:21,133
Chris...

108
00:09:26,200 --> 00:09:28,133
What? A birthday party?

109
00:09:28,200 --> 00:09:30,633
You've never had one before!

110
00:09:30,700 --> 00:09:33,233
So, we decided to throw you one.

111
00:09:33,300 --> 00:09:36,833
But my birthday is December 29th.

112
00:09:36,933 --> 00:09:38,667
That was three months ago.

113
00:09:38,767 --> 00:09:41,867
Oh, yeah... You're right.

114
00:09:41,967 --> 00:09:47,267
But it's the three-month anniversary
of your birthday!

115
00:09:48,767 --> 00:09:52,333
That's so embarrassing.
I feel like a VIP.

116
00:09:52,400 --> 00:09:54,867
That's it! VIP! VIP! VIP!

117
00:09:54,933 --> 00:09:56,500
Really? Okay.

118
00:09:56,567 --> 00:09:58,933
If you want to throw me a party,

119
00:09:59,033 --> 00:10:00,800
I'd be glad to attend.

120
00:10:00,867 --> 00:10:03,133
Yes!

121
00:10:09,400 --> 00:10:11,867
Happy birthday, Kin-chan!

122
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:17,033
Well, well, well.
Thank you very much.

123
00:10:17,100 --> 00:10:19,667
You're 22 years old!

124
00:10:20,133 --> 00:10:24,033
A long journey. How time flies!

125
00:10:24,100 --> 00:10:25,700
Which is it?

126
00:10:26,633 --> 00:10:28,867
But in my case...

127
00:10:29,233 --> 00:10:33,300
I only get better with time.
Not to brag, but...

128
00:10:34,600 --> 00:10:38,133
Okay, it's time to light the candles.

129
00:10:39,867 --> 00:10:43,067
Wow! What a huge cake!

130
00:10:43,133 --> 00:10:46,700
Chris made it with TLC.

131
00:10:48,133 --> 00:10:50,333
Oh, is that right?

132
00:10:50,400 --> 00:10:52,767
Do you like it, Kinnosuke?

133
00:10:52,833 --> 00:10:56,400
I'm not really into sweets.

134
00:10:56,467 --> 00:11:01,133
And these English cakes
are kind of over the top.

135
00:11:01,800 --> 00:11:02,733
Kin-chan!

136
00:11:08,800 --> 00:11:11,467
Wow! What a feast!

137
00:11:11,533 --> 00:11:13,800
-Right?
-Go on, eat up!

138
00:11:13,867 --> 00:11:15,500
Thank you.

139
00:11:24,667 --> 00:11:28,233
Delicious! Did you make the meat
and potatoes, Kotoko?

140
00:11:28,300 --> 00:11:30,067
Nope. Chris made it.

141
00:11:30,133 --> 00:11:35,033
Is it good, Kinnosuke?
I'm so happy!

142
00:11:35,867 --> 00:11:39,500
Maybe it was a fluke.
Let me try the other dishes.

143
00:11:40,300 --> 00:11:41,233
Here I go.

144
00:11:45,833 --> 00:11:49,267
Oh, my God! This is terrible!
What is this?

145
00:11:50,600 --> 00:11:53,533
See? This is more like it.

146
00:11:53,633 --> 00:11:56,667
Kin-chan. I made that.

147
00:11:57,533 --> 00:11:58,767
What?

148
00:11:59,533 --> 00:12:02,533
You should appreciate Chris.

149
00:12:02,600 --> 00:12:05,500
She dedicated these past six months

150
00:12:05,600 --> 00:12:08,133
to becoming a traditional
Japanese girl for you.

151
00:12:08,667 --> 00:12:11,100
Kinnosuke... here.

152
00:12:11,433 --> 00:12:15,033
It's your birthday present. Open it.

153
00:12:22,700 --> 00:12:24,533
Wow! A sweater!

154
00:12:24,600 --> 00:12:26,867
It says, "Kin!"

155
00:12:28,033 --> 00:12:30,433
And I made a matching one.

156
00:12:30,533 --> 00:12:32,467
It says, "Kuri!"

157
00:12:33,933 --> 00:12:36,633
I'm not that good at knitting,

158
00:12:36,733 --> 00:12:40,833
so it took me a while, but...

159
00:12:41,267 --> 00:12:43,467
I put my heart and soul into it.

160
00:12:45,133 --> 00:12:47,567
They're amazing!

161
00:12:47,667 --> 00:12:52,367
Maybe I'll try knitting one for Naoki.
Chris, teach me!

162
00:12:52,433 --> 00:12:55,000
I'm not a good knitter!

163
00:12:55,100 --> 00:12:59,767
But it's made with lots of love.

164
00:12:59,833 --> 00:13:03,267
Did you hear that? Love!

165
00:13:03,700 --> 00:13:05,633
Kin-chan's embarrassed.

166
00:13:05,733 --> 00:13:07,567
Oh, my God!

167
00:13:09,300 --> 00:13:12,033
Just say you're happy!

168
00:13:12,100 --> 00:13:13,200
Shut up!

169
00:13:14,533 --> 00:13:15,533
Kin-chan...?

170
00:13:16,500 --> 00:13:18,667
I've said it a hundred times.

171
00:13:18,967 --> 00:13:22,533
I love Kotoko. She's my only love.

172
00:13:23,500 --> 00:13:25,100
I don't have any feelings for you.

173
00:13:26,267 --> 00:13:27,467
Kinnosuke...

174
00:13:27,533 --> 00:13:28,633
What is this?

175
00:13:30,200 --> 00:13:33,700
Who would wear such a lame sweater?

176
00:13:34,567 --> 00:13:35,700
You...

177
00:13:36,733 --> 00:13:40,467
should hurry up
and go home to England!

178
00:13:45,767 --> 00:13:47,300
Fine!

179
00:13:48,833 --> 00:13:49,900
Chris...

180
00:13:54,767 --> 00:13:58,000
Your wish will come true.

181
00:13:59,867 --> 00:14:01,533
I'm going home.

182
00:14:09,700 --> 00:14:12,467
What is she so mad about?
How stupid.

183
00:14:15,033 --> 00:14:16,833
You're stupid!

184
00:14:19,467 --> 00:14:21,867
Chris is leaving! Don't you care?

185
00:14:21,933 --> 00:14:23,167
You're overreacting.

186
00:14:23,233 --> 00:14:26,633
She's going home to England!
Next week!

187
00:14:27,933 --> 00:14:31,333
Chris didn't want to leave.

188
00:14:31,400 --> 00:14:34,067
She tried so hard to win your heart.

189
00:14:34,600 --> 00:14:37,533
You may not feel the same way,

190
00:14:37,633 --> 00:14:40,733
but you didn't have to be so hurtful!

191
00:14:41,200 --> 00:14:42,800
You're terrible.

192
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:58,633
You all came.

193
00:14:58,733 --> 00:15:00,733
Thanks!

194
00:15:01,200 --> 00:15:04,300
You've taken such good care of me.

195
00:15:05,700 --> 00:15:07,200
Chris!

196
00:15:08,800 --> 00:15:10,133
Chris.

197
00:15:10,867 --> 00:15:12,000
Take care!

198
00:15:12,900 --> 00:15:16,167
Kotoko, I'll miss you.

199
00:15:21,300 --> 00:15:23,033
What are you doing?

200
00:15:23,100 --> 00:15:24,233
Sorry!

201
00:15:28,567 --> 00:15:30,633
What's going on, Kinnosuke?

202
00:15:30,733 --> 00:15:33,333
You're so fidgety today.

203
00:15:33,400 --> 00:15:34,933
I know why!

204
00:15:35,033 --> 00:15:36,600
Chris hasn't been here lately.

205
00:15:37,433 --> 00:15:39,133
I guess she gave up on you.

206
00:15:39,200 --> 00:15:43,600
We haven't seen her for a while.
She used to come every day.

207
00:15:44,200 --> 00:15:45,767
I kind of miss her.

208
00:15:46,000 --> 00:15:46,933
Huh?

209
00:15:47,500 --> 00:15:50,867
Boss, aren't you a little
too old for her?

210
00:15:50,933 --> 00:15:54,067
Idiot! She's like a daughter to me.

211
00:15:54,133 --> 00:15:55,067
She...

212
00:15:56,567 --> 00:15:57,967
She's leaving.

213
00:15:58,633 --> 00:15:59,467
Leaving?

214
00:16:00,300 --> 00:16:01,900
Boss!

215
00:16:02,567 --> 00:16:04,167
Boss...

216
00:16:05,233 --> 00:16:07,067
Sorry, but I need to go!

217
00:16:07,133 --> 00:16:10,333
-Go where, Kinnosuke?
-Hey, Kinnosuke!

218
00:16:10,433 --> 00:16:12,500
We're super busy today.

219
00:16:12,600 --> 00:16:15,600
Hey! Put away the dishes!

220
00:16:16,433 --> 00:16:17,267
Damn it.

221
00:16:24,233 --> 00:16:25,233
Damn it!

222
00:16:26,333 --> 00:16:29,200
I promise to write!

223
00:16:31,800 --> 00:16:33,733
It's almost time.

224
00:16:35,000 --> 00:16:37,233
Can't we wait just a little longer?

225
00:16:37,300 --> 00:16:39,800
I think Kin-chan will be here soon.

226
00:16:40,400 --> 00:16:43,900
It's okay, Kotoko. I'll be fine.

227
00:16:44,600 --> 00:16:48,000
Kotoko, you really did a good job.

228
00:16:48,933 --> 00:16:49,867
But what if

229
00:16:49,967 --> 00:16:53,800
he's on the Narita Express now?
Just a little longer.

230
00:16:54,667 --> 00:16:58,000
Thank you, Kotoko. But I give up.

231
00:16:58,067 --> 00:17:00,100
But... But...

232
00:17:00,733 --> 00:17:03,367
Thanks to Kinnosuke,

233
00:17:04,333 --> 00:17:08,933
I had so much fun in Japan.
Will you tell him that?

234
00:17:09,267 --> 00:17:10,200
Chris.

235
00:17:13,533 --> 00:17:14,567
See you!

236
00:17:15,700 --> 00:17:19,367
I'm going! Bye!

237
00:17:23,567 --> 00:17:25,167
Chris!

238
00:17:28,433 --> 00:17:32,867
But to be honest,
I was hoping he'd come.

239
00:17:34,633 --> 00:17:35,800
I wanted to...

240
00:17:38,067 --> 00:17:39,400
see him for one last time.

241
00:17:43,967 --> 00:17:44,833
Bye-bye.

242
00:17:46,800 --> 00:17:48,167
Chris.

243
00:18:08,267 --> 00:18:10,533
He didn't come.

244
00:18:14,733 --> 00:18:16,000
Let's go home.

245
00:18:21,900 --> 00:18:23,300
Chris!

246
00:18:25,067 --> 00:18:26,167
Chris!

247
00:18:28,267 --> 00:18:29,133
Kin-chan?

248
00:18:29,833 --> 00:18:31,800
Kotoko? Where's Chris?

249
00:18:33,133 --> 00:18:34,933
Kin-chan, Chris is...

250
00:18:35,733 --> 00:18:38,300
In the bathroom?
Is she in the bathroom?

251
00:18:39,467 --> 00:18:41,500
You came, Kin-chan.

252
00:18:41,800 --> 00:18:44,633
So, you really do care.

253
00:18:45,833 --> 00:18:47,533
But Chris is already...

254
00:18:47,633 --> 00:18:48,500
Kotoko...

255
00:18:53,167 --> 00:18:54,067
Sorry!

256
00:18:55,133 --> 00:18:56,267
Kin-chan...

257
00:18:58,133 --> 00:18:59,600
Chris!

258
00:19:01,500 --> 00:19:03,367
Where are you?

259
00:19:03,933 --> 00:19:04,867
Chris!

260
00:19:06,100 --> 00:19:08,033
I came for you!

261
00:19:09,000 --> 00:19:10,933
Come back!

262
00:19:12,567 --> 00:19:16,400
You're too late. She already left.

263
00:19:26,100 --> 00:19:27,100
Really?

264
00:19:30,867 --> 00:19:32,133
Chris!

265
00:19:33,233 --> 00:19:34,467
Idiot.

266
00:19:37,500 --> 00:19:39,800
Why didn't you wait for me?

267
00:19:43,133 --> 00:19:45,433
I came here for you.

268
00:19:45,500 --> 00:19:49,500
I wore this lame sweater for you.

269
00:19:50,733 --> 00:19:52,567
I went all the way home to get it.

270
00:19:55,467 --> 00:19:57,567
Look at me!

271
00:19:59,567 --> 00:20:00,667
Kin-chan.

272
00:20:02,233 --> 00:20:03,967
If he came a little earlier...

273
00:20:05,800 --> 00:20:07,200
He's too late.

274
00:20:09,967 --> 00:20:10,967
I'm starting...

275
00:20:11,967 --> 00:20:13,567
to like you a little bit.

276
00:20:14,533 --> 00:20:16,633
Stay in Japan, Chris.

277
00:20:17,500 --> 00:20:20,100
Is that true?

278
00:20:20,633 --> 00:20:24,133
Yes! So, come back!

279
00:20:24,700 --> 00:20:26,100
Chris...

280
00:20:29,067 --> 00:20:30,567
Hi, Kinnosuke.

281
00:20:33,633 --> 00:20:36,033
If that is your wish.

282
00:20:37,200 --> 00:20:38,433
Chris?

283
00:20:38,600 --> 00:20:41,300
But, Chris, your plane.

284
00:20:41,700 --> 00:20:45,867
Oh, the plane. I first got on...

285
00:20:45,933 --> 00:20:49,400
but right before it took off,

286
00:20:49,467 --> 00:20:54,433
I saw a glimpse of
Kinnosuke's face and...

287
00:20:55,500 --> 00:20:58,833
Oh, Kinnosuke. I'm so happy!

288
00:20:59,267 --> 00:21:04,233
You wore my sweater. I'm so happy!

289
00:21:04,300 --> 00:21:06,733
I meant to return it to you.
Don't be silly.

290
00:21:06,800 --> 00:21:07,867
Kinnosuke!

291
00:21:07,933 --> 00:21:10,967
Wait, wait, wait. Chris!

292
00:21:11,467 --> 00:21:14,533
Kotoko. Help me, Kotoko!

293
00:21:14,600 --> 00:21:16,633
What's the problem?

294
00:21:17,867 --> 00:21:21,900
That's enough! Get off me!

295
00:21:23,733 --> 00:21:27,267
<i>I think spring has arrived</i>
<i>for Kinnosuke.</i>

296
00:21:48,467 --> 00:21:51,667
What is this? A fashion show?

297
00:21:52,600 --> 00:21:56,633
Actually, I'm going
on a date with Naoki!

298
00:21:56,700 --> 00:21:58,933
Oh, how nice!

299
00:21:59,600 --> 00:22:01,167
Come to think of it,

300
00:22:01,233 --> 00:22:04,200
you've never been
on a real date with Naoki.

301
00:22:04,267 --> 00:22:06,000
That's right.

302
00:22:06,067 --> 00:22:09,100
Congratulations, Kotoko!

303
00:22:09,700 --> 00:22:12,200
Before the nursing exam, Naoki said:

304
00:22:13,367 --> 00:22:17,733
"If you pass the test,
I'll take you out on a date."

305
00:22:18,233 --> 00:22:21,000
That's what he said!

306
00:22:22,567 --> 00:22:26,167
