00:22:28,533 --> 00:22:30,300
Therefore, the tangent(theta)...

309
00:22:31,600 --> 00:22:32,967
What?

310
00:22:33,033 --> 00:22:34,633
Naoki...

311
00:22:34,700 --> 00:22:35,667
What is it?

312
00:22:36,167 --> 00:22:40,167
If I pass the test,
will you take me on a date?

313
00:22:41,333 --> 00:22:43,600
What are you thinking?

314
00:22:43,667 --> 00:22:48,667
I'll be way more motivated
if there's a reward in sight.

315
00:22:48,733 --> 00:22:52,500
And we've never been
on a real date.

316
00:22:52,567 --> 00:22:54,233
We're always together.

317
00:22:54,300 --> 00:22:56,833
But we've never gone out on a date.

318
00:22:56,900 --> 00:22:58,033
We went to Odaiba.

319
00:22:58,100 --> 00:23:02,700
I was following you and
Matsumoto on your date.

320
00:23:02,767 --> 00:23:06,100
That's right! You took
Matsumoto on a date!

321
00:23:06,167 --> 00:23:09,533
But not your beloved wife.
Isn't that strange?

322
00:23:10,333 --> 00:23:13,967
I want to know what it's like
to go on a date with you!

323
00:23:14,033 --> 00:23:16,300
Please, please...

324
00:23:16,367 --> 00:23:19,833
All right! All right.
So, get back to your study.

325
00:23:19,900 --> 00:23:20,900
Really?

326
00:23:21,900 --> 00:23:24,633
Yes! I'm going to do it!

327
00:23:24,733 --> 00:23:26,400
Memorize what?

328
00:23:26,467 --> 00:23:27,767
I said...

329
00:23:30,167 --> 00:23:33,233
I'm so proud of Naoki!

330
00:23:34,500 --> 00:23:38,767
We've been so busy.
It's been hard to find a free day.

331
00:23:39,500 --> 00:23:41,333
But it's tomorrow!

332
00:23:41,400 --> 00:23:42,733
-Tomorrow?
-Yes!

333
00:23:43,633 --> 00:23:46,633
So, you were choosing a date dress.

334
00:23:46,700 --> 00:23:47,533
Yes!

335
00:23:48,333 --> 00:23:49,567
How fun!

336
00:23:50,633 --> 00:23:53,400
My heart is fluttering!

337
00:23:53,467 --> 00:23:56,133
Mine, too!

338
00:23:56,200 --> 00:23:59,900
Thank goodness you passed the test.

339
00:23:59,967 --> 00:24:03,967
Naoki will be a doctor
and I will be a nurse.

340
00:24:04,533 --> 00:24:07,200
I'm one step closer to my dream.

341
00:24:07,667 --> 00:24:09,533
How wonderful!

342
00:24:10,367 --> 00:24:13,067
You must have studied very hard.

343
00:24:13,133 --> 00:24:16,400
It wasn't that bad. Actually...

344
00:24:16,467 --> 00:24:19,400
it was quite easy.

345
00:24:20,700 --> 00:24:22,000
Really?

346
00:24:23,533 --> 00:24:24,567
Naoki!

347
00:24:24,633 --> 00:24:26,500
Oh, Naoki.

348
00:24:26,567 --> 00:24:28,033
Quite easy?

349
00:24:28,500 --> 00:24:29,667
Well...

350
00:24:34,267 --> 00:24:36,400
Welcome home, Naoki.

351
00:24:40,867 --> 00:24:43,867
Naoki, speaking of our date...

352
00:24:45,600 --> 00:24:46,867
Ta-da!

353
00:24:48,033 --> 00:24:49,500
What is this?

354
00:24:51,000 --> 00:24:52,733
I stayed up all night making this.

355
00:24:53,267 --> 00:24:57,833
I hope our date tomorrow
will follow this itinerary.

356
00:24:58,333 --> 00:25:02,933
All night? Good job, Kotoko!

357
00:25:03,000 --> 00:25:05,933
Naoki is such a lucky guy.

358
00:25:07,700 --> 00:25:11,767
You should be using your time
to study nursing instead.

359
00:25:15,100 --> 00:25:16,067
Oh, my.

360
00:25:17,267 --> 00:25:18,767
It's a secret. Top secret.

361
00:25:26,033 --> 00:25:28,033
-Good morning, Naoki.
-Morning.

362
00:25:29,167 --> 00:25:30,967
Naoki, you're still here?

363
00:25:31,900 --> 00:25:33,300
Still here?

364
00:25:33,667 --> 00:25:35,600
Your date is today.

365
00:25:35,667 --> 00:25:39,333
What are you still doing here?
Kotoko already left!

366
00:25:39,433 --> 00:25:42,400
We're supposed to meet at noon.

367
00:25:45,367 --> 00:25:49,733
Oh, it's a little early, then.

368
00:25:49,833 --> 00:25:52,067
Her head is in the clouds.

369
00:25:52,367 --> 00:25:55,433
What is she thinking?
Leaving so early...

370
00:25:56,067 --> 00:25:57,200
I don't get it.

371
00:25:57,267 --> 00:26:00,767
Why should we meet somewhere
when we live in the same house?

372
00:26:14,767 --> 00:26:17,467
Yes! The best spot!

373
00:26:17,900 --> 00:26:22,500
Let me review the itinerary.

374
00:26:34,433 --> 00:26:36,033
<i>Eleven-thirty a.m.</i>

375
00:26:36,100 --> 00:26:40,800
<i>Naoki arrives at our meeting spot</i>
<i>30 minutes ahead of time.</i>

376
00:26:43,767 --> 00:26:45,767
I'm way too early.

377
00:26:55,500 --> 00:27:00,867
<i>Naoki is waiting for me.</i>
<i>He looks a bit nervous.</i>

378
00:27:05,000 --> 00:27:06,300
<i>Twelve-o-five p.m.</i>

379
00:27:06,367 --> 00:27:10,667
<i>I arrive just a few minutes late!</i>

380
00:27:33,433 --> 00:27:35,600
Sorry. Did you wait long?

381
00:27:36,033 --> 00:27:38,033
No, I just got here.

382
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:39,867
I'm really sorry.

383
00:27:40,867 --> 00:27:43,967
You're here now.
That's all that matters.

384
00:27:45,633 --> 00:27:46,700
Naoki.

385
00:28:05,067 --> 00:28:08,500
This is it. This is it!

386
00:28:10,200 --> 00:28:11,200
Okay!

387
00:28:13,867 --> 00:28:16,600
I wish he'd hurry up.

388
00:28:29,033 --> 00:28:31,767
He knows it's today, right?

389
00:28:41,000 --> 00:28:43,700
He never picks up his phone.

390
00:28:45,100 --> 00:28:48,167
What if something happened?

391
00:28:48,967 --> 00:28:52,200
An accident? Oh, no!

392
00:28:53,200 --> 00:28:55,767
If something happens to him, I'll...

393
00:28:58,833 --> 00:29:00,367
What are you doing here?

394
00:29:02,267 --> 00:29:03,533
Naoki!

395
00:29:03,600 --> 00:29:05,633
We're meeting on the bridge, right?

396
00:29:05,700 --> 00:29:08,833
Naoki, thank God you're safe!

397
00:29:10,900 --> 00:29:14,367
<i>I can't let on that I was</i>
<i>watching from here!</i>

398
00:29:15,733 --> 00:29:18,867
Did you just arrive?
What a coincidence!

399
00:29:18,933 --> 00:29:19,900
Why...

400
00:29:19,967 --> 00:29:23,867
did you leave the house
two hours early to hide here?

401
00:29:24,500 --> 00:29:25,367
I'm busted.

402
00:29:26,100 --> 00:29:28,833
It was you who told me to be here
at the bridge at noon.

403
00:29:29,633 --> 00:29:31,033
I don't get it.

404
00:29:33,000 --> 00:29:35,200
-Well...
-Let's go.

405
00:29:35,267 --> 00:29:37,500
<i>Not a very good start.</i>

406
00:29:38,233 --> 00:29:40,733
<i>No! Our date is only beginning!</i>

407
00:29:40,800 --> 00:29:43,700
<i>Our dream date. Let's go!</i>

408
00:29:46,467 --> 00:29:48,133
I prefer an action film.

409
00:29:49,533 --> 00:29:51,333
I already bought our tickets.

410
00:29:52,800 --> 00:29:54,033
Ta-da!

411
00:29:54,767 --> 00:29:58,767
<i>Eternal Love.</i> It's supposed
to be so romantic!

412
00:30:20,367 --> 00:30:21,467
Naoki...

413
00:30:57,400 --> 00:31:01,567
Here are our seats.

414
00:31:17,667 --> 00:31:19,367
<i>Is he going to...</i>

415
00:31:19,933 --> 00:31:22,900
<i>hold my hand?</i>

416
00:31:34,900 --> 00:31:36,700
Naoki...

417
00:31:40,067 --> 00:31:41,000
Kotoko.

418
00:31:42,967 --> 00:31:44,033
Wake up.

419
00:31:45,433 --> 00:31:51,200
But, Naoki...

420
00:31:57,600 --> 00:31:59,033
The movie's over.

421
00:32:03,133 --> 00:32:04,100
Let's go.

422
00:32:14,067 --> 00:32:18,467
I wanted to enjoy
the beautiful outdoors with you.

423
00:32:37,167 --> 00:32:40,967
I heard that couples that
ride the boats in this park--

424
00:32:41,033 --> 00:32:43,167
Let's ride the boat, Naoki!

425
00:32:44,100 --> 00:32:45,333
Hurry!

426
00:32:47,200 --> 00:32:49,000
Hurry!

427
00:32:52,333 --> 00:32:55,833
Excuse me. Can we rent a boat?

428
00:32:55,900 --> 00:32:57,433
That will be 400 yen.

429
00:32:57,500 --> 00:32:59,867
-Okay.
-Wait a minute, Kotoko.

430
00:33:00,800 --> 00:33:02,233
I'm going to buy some drinks.

431
00:33:02,300 --> 00:33:03,267
Now?

432
00:33:04,100 --> 00:33:05,500
We can drink them on the boat.

433
00:33:06,100 --> 00:33:07,433
Sorry. I'll be right back.

434
00:33:08,467 --> 00:33:09,433
Okay.

435
00:33:10,400 --> 00:33:11,267
Naoki!

436
00:33:18,433 --> 00:33:23,000
Where is Naoki? How far did he go?

437
00:33:23,733 --> 00:33:26,000
Kazuhiko, what's wrong?

438
00:33:26,633 --> 00:33:28,500
Are you okay? Are you okay?

439
00:33:30,600 --> 00:33:33,733
Kazuhiko... are you okay?

440
00:33:34,667 --> 00:33:37,000
What's wrong? Kazuhiko!

441
00:33:38,667 --> 00:33:40,767
-Kazuhiko...
-What's wrong?

442
00:33:40,833 --> 00:33:43,033
My son... he suddenly...

443
00:33:44,200 --> 00:33:46,033
Are you all right?

444
00:33:47,967 --> 00:33:51,367
He can't breathe!
Can I loosen his buttons?

445
00:33:51,433 --> 00:33:53,000
-Yes.
-Okay.

446
00:33:55,933 --> 00:33:59,100
-Are you okay?
-Kazuhiko...

447
00:34:00,333 --> 00:34:02,367
-Kotoko!
-Naoki!

448
00:34:04,033 --> 00:34:05,200
What happened?

449
00:34:05,300 --> 00:34:06,333
I don't know.

450
00:34:06,433 --> 00:34:08,567
He started coughing
and couldn't stop.

451
00:34:09,267 --> 00:34:11,500
Does your son have asthma?

452
00:34:11,567 --> 00:34:12,833
I don't think so.

453
00:34:13,133 --> 00:34:14,967
Let's lay him down on the bench.

454
00:34:15,033 --> 00:34:17,767
He'll breathe easier
if he's sitting up.

455
00:34:18,667 --> 00:34:21,700
Hold him up like this.

456
00:34:22,233 --> 00:34:23,733
-Call an ambulance.
-Okay.

457
00:34:27,400 --> 00:34:29,467
Can you suck on this?

458
00:34:32,767 --> 00:34:37,267
Hello? A 5-year-old
is having trouble breathing.

459
00:34:38,200 --> 00:34:39,100
You'll feel better.

460
00:34:43,400 --> 00:34:44,400
Do you? Kazuhiko!

461
00:34:49,033 --> 00:34:50,767
Breathe in.

462
00:34:52,533 --> 00:34:54,467
Breathe out.

463
00:35:05,167 --> 00:35:08,167
I want to play basketball next year.

464
00:35:08,267 --> 00:35:10,300
You'll have to work hard, then.

465
00:35:10,900 --> 00:35:11,867
Okay!

466
00:35:23,500 --> 00:35:25,500
Thank you so much.

467
00:35:26,167 --> 00:35:27,500
How is he?

468
00:35:27,567 --> 00:35:32,467
The doctor is with him now.
His condition is stable.

469
00:35:33,533 --> 00:35:36,200
I don't know how to thank you.

470
00:35:36,600 --> 00:35:37,533
Not at all.

471
00:35:37,967 --> 00:35:40,800
The doctor said it's a good thing
we brought him in quickly.

472
00:35:40,900 --> 00:35:42,500
That's good...

473
00:35:42,733 --> 00:35:44,433
What did he say it was?

474
00:35:45,400 --> 00:35:47,300
He thinks it's bronchial asthma.

475
00:35:47,733 --> 00:35:48,567
I see.

476
00:35:48,633 --> 00:35:53,933
He's been coughing a lot lately.
I thought it was a cold...

477
00:35:54,833 --> 00:35:57,833
Asthma is sometimes
triggered by a cold.

478
00:35:58,367 --> 00:36:01,600
It's easy to control with medication.

479
00:36:01,667 --> 00:36:04,600
It's a very treatable condition,

480
00:36:04,867 --> 00:36:08,200
so, don't worry too much.

481
00:36:08,833 --> 00:36:10,967
Oh... okay.

482
00:36:12,067 --> 00:36:14,433
He's going to be a doctor.

483
00:36:16,600 --> 00:36:19,100
Oh, is that why?

484
00:36:20,300 --> 00:36:23,167
Thank you very much.

485
00:36:31,500 --> 00:36:34,000
I was a bit shocked just now.

486
00:36:35,133 --> 00:36:36,133
What?

487
00:36:36,967 --> 00:36:41,033
You're usually so cool, but you
really empathized with his mom.

488
00:36:43,067 --> 00:36:44,467
Of course.

489
00:36:46,533 --> 00:36:47,733
I know, but...

490
00:36:49,600 --> 00:36:50,800
But...

491
00:36:53,300 --> 00:36:54,167
What?

492
00:36:56,900 --> 00:36:57,833
You...

493
00:36:59,433 --> 00:37:01,667
were like a real doctor.

494
00:37:03,933 --> 00:37:05,300
Idiot.

495
00:37:07,400 --> 00:37:11,233
There are a lot of sick kids,
aren't there?

496
00:37:13,367 --> 00:37:14,300
Yeah.

497
00:37:16,233 --> 00:37:17,333
But...

498
00:37:18,067 --> 00:37:23,267
when you become a doctor,
you can help them.

499
00:37:24,467 --> 00:37:25,833
It's not that easy.

500
00:37:27,133 --> 00:37:29,100
When you become a doctor,

501
00:37:29,167 --> 00:37:32,233
you'll save many children's lives.

502
00:37:35,300 --> 00:37:37,233
You'd better hurry up.

503
00:37:39,033 --> 00:37:44,267
You'd better become a nurse, too.

504
00:37:44,333 --> 00:37:49,300
Don't worry! I'll be
a bona fide nurse in three years.

505
00:37:51,100 --> 00:37:56,400
You have to pass a national exam
to become a nurse, you know.

506
00:37:57,167 --> 00:37:58,600
Another test?

507
00:38:02,167 --> 00:38:04,167
Wait, Naoki.

508
00:38:08,933 --> 00:38:13,033
You were a pretty good nurse today.

509
00:38:27,600 --> 00:38:29,767
They're already closed.

510
00:38:30,467 --> 00:38:31,600
Yeah.

511
00:38:33,167 --> 00:38:35,833
Oh, it's you!

512
00:38:39,333 --> 00:38:42,267
Is it too late to rent a boat?

513
00:38:53,733 --> 00:38:55,967
He saw everything, didn't he?

514
00:38:56,033 --> 00:38:59,333
He let us take the boat
because we helped that boy.

515
00:39:00,400 --> 00:39:01,400
Yeah.

516
00:39:09,633 --> 00:39:12,667
This is a little different
from the date I imagined.

517
00:39:13,833 --> 00:39:16,900
I had all these grand plans in my head

518
00:39:16,967 --> 00:39:20,900
but it's no fun when things go
exactly as planned.

519
00:39:20,967 --> 00:39:23,933
As long as I can be with you...

520
00:39:24,000 --> 00:39:25,400
I'm happy.

521
00:39:29,133 --> 00:39:29,967
What?

522
00:39:31,267 --> 00:39:33,133
Didn't you know?

523
00:39:34,167 --> 00:39:38,133
Couples who ride these boats
are fated to part ways.

524
00:39:38,200 --> 00:39:39,500
What?

525
00:39:40,067 --> 00:39:42,800
The goddess of this park...

526
00:39:43,233 --> 00:39:46,700
is a jealous spirit that
likes to break couples up.

527
00:39:46,800 --> 00:39:49,700
-Oh, my God!
-Don't stand up!

528
00:39:50,800 --> 00:39:53,500
You mean you knew that?

529
00:39:54,967 --> 00:39:57,967
What do you want to do?
We're on the boat already.

530
00:39:59,767 --> 00:40:03,467
Why didn't you tell me
before we got on?

531
00:40:04,267 --> 00:40:05,967
I would never have...

532
00:40:12,033 --> 00:40:14,267
This is the kind of date
you envisioned, right?

533
00:40:15,000 --> 00:40:17,767
You and me, on a boat.

534
00:40:19,167 --> 00:40:20,667
Naoki, how did you...?

535
00:40:20,733 --> 00:40:22,233
What else?

536
00:40:22,900 --> 00:40:25,633
Holding hands at the movies.

537
00:40:26,600 --> 00:40:29,733
Me arriving 30 minutes early.

538
00:40:31,033 --> 00:40:33,867
Naoki, did you know everything?

539
00:40:34,433 --> 00:40:36,700
I wonder.

540
00:40:36,867 --> 00:40:39,767
I can't believe it!

541
00:40:39,867 --> 00:40:42,400
When did you read my plan?

542
00:40:43,367 --> 00:40:48,300
I'd never agree on a date
exactly as you planned it,

543
00:40:48,767 --> 00:40:51,400
but you stayed up
all night planning it out.

544
00:40:52,767 --> 00:40:55,367
The least I could do was
make part of it come true.

545
00:40:57,267 --> 00:40:58,400
